The paper deals with weakly supervised semantic segmentation using CNN-based methods, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel method for extracting accurate masks from pre-trained networks, which involves using higher-level convolutional layers and a dense CRF, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of image tags, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper introduces a new form of weak supervision, which could potentially involve the use of neural networks (cs.NE).
